cs.IT, cs.ET, cs.AR, cs.DS, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper investigates the scaling behavior of the minimum total power needed to communicate over AWGN channels, which is a fundamental problem in information theory. 
2. cs.ET (Embedded Systems) - The paper analyzes the VLSI complexity models of decoding, which is related to embedded systems design. 
3. cs.AR (Architecture) - The paper develops detailed physical models of decoding implementations using post-layout circuit simulations, which is related to computer architecture. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the complexity of the code design and the corresponding decoding algorithm, which is related to data structures and algorithms. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper investigates the total power capacity of communication systems, which is related to systems and control.
